    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately not assessed at this model risk level. The 13-factor ASME V&V 40 matrix is complete. Assurance level is declared High based on the elevated breadth of the validation campaign, including a three-level mesh convergence study and geometric sensitivity sweep. The assessment team concludes the CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device within the stated COU. The relative hemolysis index predictions across all five flow-speed combinations satisfy RH < 1.0, supporting the Accepted decision.",
